1, 25 - Dihydroxy Vitamin D
description: Active form of vitamin D test - Measures the biologically active form of vitamin D to help diagnose disorders related to calcium metabolism.

name: 25 - Hydroxyvit D2 & D3
description: Comprehensive vitamin D test - Measures both forms of vitamin D (D2 and D3) to assess overall vitamin D status and potential deficiencies.

name: A. Phagocytophilum ABS
description: Antibody test for Anaplasma phagocytophilum - Detects antibodies to the bacteria that causes anaplasmosis, a tick-borne illness.

name: Affirm Panel for : Trichomonas DNA Gardnerella DNA Candida DNA Probe
description: Comprehensive vaginal infection panel - Tests for three common causes of vaginal infections using DNA analysis: Trichomonas, Gardnerella (bacterial vaginosis), and Candida (yeast).

name: Albumin
description: Albumin blood test - Measures levels of albumin, the main protein in blood, to evaluate liver and kidney function and nutritional status.

name: Albumin, Urine, W/ Creat
description: Urine albumin to creatinine ratio test - Checks for kidney damage by measuring the ratio of albumin to creatinine in a random urine sample.

name: Alcohols - Ethanol
description: Blood alcohol test - Measures the concentration of ethanol (drinking alcohol) in the blood to determine intoxication levels.

name: Alkaline Phosphatase
description: Alkaline phosphatase (ALP) test - Measures the level of this enzyme to help detect liver disease or bone disorders.

name: Allergy Panel
description: Comprehensive environmental allergy test - Tests for IgE antibodies to common allergens including dust mites, animal dander, molds, and other environmental triggers.

name: Allergy Panel, Food II
description: Food allergy panel - Tests for IgE antibodies to various food allergens including strawberry, yeast, oats, corn, orange, coconut, and chicken.

name: Allegy Panel, Household
description: Household allergen panel - Tests for IgE antibodies to common household allergens that may trigger allergic reactions in the home environment.

name: Allergy Profile, Seasonal
description: Comprehensive seasonal allergen profile - Tests for IgE antibodies to a wide range of seasonal allergens from grasses, weeds, and trees.

name: ALT (SGPT)
description: Alanine aminotransferase test - Measures this liver enzyme to detect liver damage or disease.

name: Amphetamine Confirm
description: Confirmatory test for amphetamines - Quantitative analysis that confirms the presence and amount of amphetamines in the system.

name: Amylase
description: Amylase test - Measures levels of this digestive enzyme to help diagnose pancreatic disorders or inflammation.

name: Amylase/ Lipase
description: Combined pancreatic enzyme test - Measures both amylase and lipase levels, commonly used to diagnose pancreatitis or other pancreatic disorders.

name: ANA Cascade
description: Antinuclear antibody cascade test - Initial screening for autoimmune disorders with automatic reflex testing for DsDNA and ENA if positive.

name: Ana Multiplex, Rfx Titer
description: Antinuclear antibody multiplex test - Advanced test that identifies specific autoantibodies with reflex titer if positive, useful for diagnosing various autoimmune disorders.

name: Ana Titer And Pattern, IFA
description: ANA pattern and titer by immunofluorescence - Detailed analysis of antinuclear antibodies that helps categorize autoimmune disorders based on antibody patterns.

name: Anti Thyroglobulin AB
description: Anti-thyroglobulin antibody test - Measures antibodies against thyroglobulin to help diagnose autoimmune thyroid disorders.

name: ANA by IFA Reflex to Titer/ Pattern
description: ANA screening with reflex testing - Initial screening for antinuclear antibodies with automatic additional testing for pattern and concentration if positive.

name: Apolipoprotein A1
description: Apolipoprotein A1 test - Measures levels of this protein component of HDL (good cholesterol) to assess cardiovascular risk.

name: Apolipoprotein B
description: Apolipoprotein B test - Measures levels of this protein found in LDL (bad cholesterol) to help determine risk of heart disease and stroke.

name: Arthritis Panel (AMA)
description: Comprehensive arthritis evaluation - Includes uric acid, sedimentation rate, ANA tests, and rheumatoid factor to help diagnose various types of arthritis.

name: AST (SGOT)
description: Aspartate aminotransferase test - Measures this enzyme to detect liver damage or disease, also used to monitor liver function.

name: B. Pertussis Toxin AB, IGG
description: Bordetella pertussis toxin antibody test - Detects IgG antibodies to whooping cough bacteria to confirm recent or past infection.

name: Babesia Microti ABS (IGG /lGM), IFA
description: Babesia microti antibody test - Detects antibodies to this tick-borne parasite that causes babesiosis, an infection similar to malaria.

name: Babesia Serology
description: Babesia antibody blood test - Detects antibodies to Babesia parasites, useful in diagnosing this tick-borne illness.

name: Bacterial Vaginosis Assoc Bact 2
description: Bacterial vaginosis test - Detects bacteria associated with bacterial vaginosis using a single swab specimen.

name: Basic Met. Panel W/ GFR
description: Basic metabolic panel with GFR - Measures kidney function, electrolyte and fluid balance, and blood sugar levels.

name: Basic Metabolic PNL (AMA)
description: Comprehensive metabolic panel - Evaluates kidney and liver function, electrolyte and acid/base balance, blood sugar, and protein levels.

name: Benzodiazepine Confirm
description: Confirmatory test that identifies and quantifies specific benzodiazepine compounds in a sample following a positive screening result.

name: Bilirubin, Direct
description: Direct bilirubin test - Measures the conjugated form of bilirubin to help diagnose liver disease or bile duct blockages.

name: Bilirubin, Total
description: Total bilirubin test - Measures all bilirubin in the blood to screen for liver problems or evaluate jaundice.

name: Bill Betalact
description: Beta-lactam allergy test - Used for billing purposes to test for allergies to beta-lactam antibiotics like penicillin.

name: Blood Culture
description: Blood culture test - Detects bacteria or fungi in the bloodstream to diagnose bloodstream infections (sepsis).

name: Blood Culture 2
description: Second blood culture test - Additional sample collection to increase accuracy when diagnosing bloodstream infections.

name: Blood Group/ Rh Factor
description: Blood typing test - Determines ABO blood group (A, B, AB, O) and Rh factor (positive or negative) for transfusions, pregnancy care, and other medical needs.

name: Blood GRP/ RH Factor /AB Screen
description: Comprehensive blood typing with antibody screen - Determines blood type and checks for unexpected antibodies that could cause transfusion reactions.

name: BNP Evaluation
description: B-type natriuretic peptide test - Measures the level of this heart failure marker to help diagnose and monitor heart failure.

name: BV, Candida, STI Panel
description: Comprehensive genital health panel - Tests for bacterial vaginosis, yeast infections, and sexually transmitted infections with a single swab.

name: C-Reactive Protein
description: C-reactive protein test - Measures this inflammation marker to detect inflammation throughout the body.

name: C. Trachomatis, Amplif
description: Chlamydia trachomatis amplified test - Uses nucleic acid amplification to detect chlamydia bacteria with high sensitivity.

name: C. Albicans Fluconazole
description: Candida albicans fluconazole susceptibility test - Determines if this yeast infection will respond to fluconazole antifungal medication.

name: CA-125 (Roche Eclia)
description: Cancer antigen 125 test - Primarily used to monitor ovarian cancer treatment or as part of evaluation for ovarian masses.

name: Calcium
description: Calcium blood test - Measures calcium levels to evaluate parathyroid function, bone health, and other calcium-related disorders.

name: Calcium Urine, Random
description: Random urine calcium test - Measures calcium levels in urine to evaluate kidney stone risk or calcium metabolism disorders.

name: Calcium, Ionized
description: Ionized calcium test - Measures the active (free) form of calcium in blood for more precise evaluation of calcium status.

name: Calcium/Phosphorous
description: Combined calcium and phosphorus test - Evaluates the balance between these two minerals related to bone health, kidney function, and parathyroid issues.

name: Candida Albicans, PCR
description: Candida albicans PCR test - Detects DNA of the yeast that causes common fungal infections using highly sensitive molecular methods.

name: Candida Glabrata PCR
description: Candida glabrata PCR test - Detects DNA of this specific yeast species, which can cause vaginal infections and is often resistant to common antifungals.

name: Candida Vaginitis Panel
description: Comprehensive yeast infection panel - Tests for multiple Candida species (albicans, tropicalis, parapsilosis, glabrata) using PCR methodology from a single swab.

name: Carbon Dioxide
description: CO2 blood test - Measures bicarbonate levels to evaluate acid-base balance, respiratory function, and kidney function.

name: Cardiac Enzymes
description: Cardiac enzyme panel - Measures enzymes (LDH, CPK, AST) released during heart damage to help diagnose heart attacks and cardiac injury.

name: Cardiolipin ABS (lgG/ lgA/ lgM)
description: Cardiolipin antibody test - Detects antibodies associated with antiphospholipid syndrome, which can cause abnormal blood clotting and pregnancy complications.

name: CBC With Platelet
description: Complete blood count with platelet count - Evaluates overall health and screens for various disorders by measuring red cells, white cells, and platelets.

name: CBC-Lead
description: Complete blood count with lead testing - Combines blood cell analysis with lead level testing to screen for lead exposure and its effects on blood cells.

name: CBC/ Platelet/ Differential
description: Complete blood count with differential - Comprehensive blood cell analysis including detailed white blood cell breakdown and red cell evaluation.

name: CEA (Roche Eclia)
description: Carcinoembryonic antigen test - Tumor marker primarily used to monitor colorectal cancer treatment and detect recurrence.

name: Chlamydia Trach Culture
description: Chlamydia trachomatis culture - Grows and identifies chlamydia bacteria to diagnose this common sexually transmitted infection.

name: Chlamydia Trachomatis, RT- PCR
description: Chlamydia RT-PCR test - Highly sensitive molecular test that detects chlamydia genetic material to diagnose infection.

name: Chlamydia Trachomatis, Urine, Amplified
description: Urine-based chlamydia test - Non-invasive test using urine sample to detect chlamydia with amplified DNA/RNA technology.

name: Chlamydia, GC, Trichomonas
description: Combined STI panel - Tests urine sample for three common sexually transmitted infections: chlamydia, gonorrhea, and trichomonas.

name: Chlamydia/GC Amplified, Ur
description: Urine test that detects both chlamydia and gonorrhea infections using amplified DNA technology. Less invasive alternative to swab testing.

name: Chlamydia/Gonorrhea, Ampli
description: Comprehensive amplified DNA test for detecting both chlamydia and gonorrhea infections. More sensitive than traditional culture methods.

name: Chloride
description: Measures chloride levels in the blood, which helps evaluate electrolyte balance and acid-base status. Important for kidney and hydration assessment.

name: Clostridium Difficile
description: Tests for C. difficile bacteria that can cause severe diarrhea and colon inflammation. Uses toxin/GDH testing with reflex to PCR for more accurate results.

name: Comp Metabolic Panel (AMA)
description: Comprehensive panel that evaluates organ function, electrolyte balance, blood sugar, and protein levels. Includes 14 different tests to assess overall health.

name: Complete Blood Count
description: Basic blood test that counts red and white blood cells, hemoglobin, hematocrit, and other blood components. Screens for anemia, infection, and other disorders.

name: Comprehensive Metabolic with GFR
description: Extended metabolic panel that includes kidney function test (GFR). Evaluates organ function, electrolytes, blood sugar, and protein status.

name: Comprehensive Metabolic
description: Panel of 14 tests that provides information about metabolism, kidney and liver function, electrolyte levels, blood sugar, and protein levels in the blood.

name: Cortisol, Resting
description: Measures the level of cortisol (stress hormone) at rest. Helps diagnose adrenal disorders like Cushing's syndrome or Addison's disease.

name: CPK
description: Creatine Phosphokinase test that measures an enzyme found primarily in the heart, brain, and skeletal muscle. Used to detect muscle damage or heart attack.

name: Creatinine Urine/ Microalb
description: Measures urinary creatinine and microalbumin levels to assess kidney function and detect early signs of kidney damage. Critical for monitoring diabetic nephropathy and other kidney conditions.

name: Creatinine With GFR
description: Measures kidney function by testing creatinine levels and calculating glomerular filtration rate (GFR). Important for evaluating kidney health and disease.

name: CRP Highly Sens
description: High-sensitivity C-Reactive Protein test that detects low levels of inflammation. Used to evaluate risk for heart disease and monitor inflammatory conditions.

name: Culture Aerobic/Anaerobic
description: Bacterial culture that tests for both oxygen-dependent (aerobic) and oxygen-independent (anaerobic) bacteria to identify infections.

name: Culture, Feces
description: Stool culture test that identifies bacterial infections in the digestive tract. Helps diagnose causes of persistent diarrhea, food poisoning, or intestinal diseases.

name: Culture, Genital (Swab)
description: Genital swab culture to identify bacterial infections or STIs. Base price shown; additional charges may apply for specific bacteria identification.

name: Culture, Staph Aureus
description: Culture specific for detecting methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA). Identifies antibiotic-resistant staph infections.

name: Culture, General w/ Sensitivities
description: General bacterial culture with antibiotic sensitivity testing. Identifies infections and determines which antibiotics will be most effective for treatment.

name: Culture, Wound w/ Sens.
description: Wound culture with antibiotic sensitivity testing. Identifies bacteria causing wound infections and determines effective antibiotics for treatment.

name: D-Dimer Plasma
description: Tests for D-dimer protein fragments that indicate blood clot formation or dissolution. Used to help diagnose blood clots, DVT, or pulmonary embolism.

name: Dhea, Serum
description: Measures DHEA (dehydroepiandrosterone) hormone levels in the blood. Helps evaluate adrenal function and can indicate certain hormonal disorders.

name: Differential
description: Detailed analysis of white blood cell types and counts. Helps diagnose infections, inflammations, leukemia, and immune disorders.

name: Digoxin
description: Measures levels of digoxin medication in the blood. Monitors therapeutic levels and prevents toxicity in patients taking this heart medication.

name: Diptheria Toxid IgG
description: Measures antibodies against diphtheria toxoid. Helps determine immunity status and whether vaccination is needed.

name: Drug Abuse-10 Pnl W/Conf
description: Comprehensive 10-panel drug screening with confirmation testing. Detects presence of commonly abused drugs and confirms positive results with additional testing.

name: Drug Screen (Urine)
description: Forensic-quality urine test that screens for presence of drugs of abuse. Results can be used for legal or employment purposes.

name: Drugs Abuse, Oral Fluid Pnl, Rflx to Confirmation
description: Oral fluid drug testing panel with automatic confirmation testing for positive results. Less invasive alternative to urine testing.

name: dsDNA Antibody
description: Tests for antibodies against double-stranded DNA. Important marker for diagnosing and monitoring systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE).

name: DU Variant
description: Tests for DU variant (weak D antigen) in Rh blood typing. Important for pregnancy and transfusion compatibility.

name: EB Viral Studies
description: Comprehensive Epstein-Barr virus testing. Helps diagnose infectious mononucleosis (mono) and determine the stage of infection.

name: EBV-Nuclear Antigen. IgG
description: Tests for IgG antibodies against Epstein-Barr virus nuclear antigen. Indicates past infection with EBV (mono).

name: EBV-Viral Capsid AG., lGG
description: Measures IgG antibodies against EBV viral capsid antigen. Helps determine previous exposure to Epstein-Barr virus.

name: Epstein & Mono Pnl
description: Complete panel for diagnosing mononucleosis and EBV infection. Includes rapid mono test and specific EBV antibody tests.

name: ESR/ RA
description: Combined test measuring erythrocyte sedimentation rate and rheumatoid arthritis factor. Screens for inflammation and autoimmune conditions.

name: ESR, Westergren (Lavender Tube)
description: Erythrocyte sedimentation rate test using the Westergren method. Non-specific marker for inflammation and infection in the body.

name: Ethyl Alcohol Quant, Ur
description: Quantitative confirmation test for ethyl alcohol (ethanol) in urine. Provides precise measurement of alcohol concentration.

name: Ferritin
description: Measures iron storage protein in the blood. Key test for diagnosing iron deficiency anemia or iron overload conditions.

name: Folate, Serum
description: Measures folate (vitamin B9) levels in blood. Important for detecting deficiencies that can cause anemia and neural tube defects in pregnancy.

name: Follicle Stim. Hormone
description: Measures FSH hormone levels. Important for evaluating fertility, menopause, or pituitary gland function.

name: Free T-4
description: Measures free (unbound) thyroxine hormone in blood. Most accurate indicator of thyroid function and important for diagnosing thyroid disorders.

name: FSH
description: Follicle Stimulating Hormone test. Evaluates fertility, menstrual problems, or pituitary gland function.

name: FSH/ LH Profile
description: Combined profile measuring both Follicle Stimulating Hormone and Luteinizing Hormone. Used for fertility assessment and reproductive health evaluation.

name: FSH/ LH/ Estradiol
description: Comprehensive female hormone panel that measures FSH, LH, and estradiol. Used to evaluate fertility, menopause, and ovarian function.

name: FTA/ ABS
description: Fluorescent Treponemal Antibody Absorption test. Specific test for confirming syphilis infection.

name: GC Culture,Throat
description: Throat culture specifically testing for gonorrhea bacteria. Used to detect oral/pharyngeal gonorrhea infections.

name: Glucose
description: Basic blood sugar test that measures glucose levels. Used to screen for diabetes or monitor blood sugar control.

name: Glucose - 3 Samples
description: Three separate glucose measurements, typically performed during glucose tolerance testing. Used to diagnose diabetes or other glucose metabolism disorders.

name: H.Pylori Antigen, Stool
description: Stool test that directly detects H. pylori bacterial antigens. Used to diagnose H. pylori infection that can cause ulcers and gastritis.

name: H.Pylori Breath Test
description: Non-invasive breath test that detects H. pylori bacterial infection. Patient breathes into a device after consuming a test substance.

name: Hair 5 Drug Panel
description: Hair sample test that screens for drug use over a longer time period (typically 90 days). Detects 5 common drug categories.

name: HBSAG Confirmation
description: Confirmatory test for Hepatitis B surface antigen. Verifies positive results from initial screening to confirm Hepatitis B infection.

name: HCG, Quantitative Levels (already Preg.)
description: Precise measurement of pregnancy hormone (HCG) levels. Used to monitor pregnancy progress or complications in confirmed pregnancies.

name: HVC NAAT W/ Reflex HCV Geno
description: Advanced Hepatitis C test with automatic genotype testing if positive. Detects viral RNA and determines the specific strain for treatment planning.

name: HCV PCR Quant
description: Quantitative PCR test measuring Hepatitis C viral load. Used to confirm infection and monitor treatment response.

name: Hemoglobin A1c (Lavender Tube)
description: Measures average blood sugar levels over the past 2-3 months. Essential test for diagnosing and monitoring diabetes management.

name: Hemoglobin Electro.
description: Analyzes different types of hemoglobin in the blood. Used to diagnose sickle cell disease, thalassemia, and other hemoglobin disorders.

name: Hemoglobin & Hematocrit
description: Measures red blood cell count and concentration. Basic test for diagnosing anemia and evaluating blood disorders.

name: Hepatic Function Panel (AMA)
description: Comprehensive liver function testing panel. Evaluates liver health, function, and detects liver disease or damage.

name: Hepatitis A Total W/ Reflex to lgM
description: Tests for total Hepatitis A antibodies with automatic IgM testing if positive. Differentiates between current and past infection.

name: Hepatitis A Profile
description: Complete Hepatitis A testing profile. Determines current infection status, past exposure, and immunity to the virus.

name: Hepatitis A Total ABS
description: Measures total antibodies (IgG and IgM) to Hepatitis A virus. Shows current or previous infection or vaccination status.

name: Hepatitis A, IgM
description: Tests specifically for IgM antibodies to Hepatitis A. Positive results indicate recent or current infection.

name: Hepatitis B Anti, Quantat
description: Quantitative test measuring antibody levels against Hepatitis B. Used to check immunity after vaccination or past infection.

name: Hepatitis B Core AB, IgM
description: Test for recent or active Hepatitis B infection. Detects IgM antibodies that appear early in the infection process.

name: Hepatitis B Core AB, Total
description: Measures all antibodies (both IgM and IgG) to the Hepatitis B core antigen, indicating current or past infection with Hepatitis B virus.

name: Hepatitis BS Antigen
description: Tests for the surface antigen of the Hepatitis B virus, indicating an active Hepatitis B infection. Used for screening and diagnosis.

name: Hepatitis BS Antibody
description: Detects antibodies to the Hepatitis B surface antigen, indicating either past infection or vaccination against Hepatitis B. Used for immigration screening.

name: Hepatitis BE Antibody
description: Tests for antibodies to the Hepatitis B e antigen, which helps determine the stage of Hepatitis B infection and infectivity.

name: Hepatitis C AB Reflex HCV RNA Quant
description: Initial screening test for Hepatitis C antibodies with automatic follow-up testing to measure viral load if antibodies are detected.

name: Hepatitis Panel Ama
description: Comprehensive panel testing for Hepatitis A, B, and C infections. Includes tests for active infections and previous exposure.

name: Hepatitis Panel(Ama)
description: Expanded hepatitis screening panel that includes multiple markers for Hepatitis A, B, and C to determine current infection status, immunity, and past exposure.

name: Hepatitis Profile-Comp. (Hepatitis A, B, C, with Reflex)
Herpes I And II
description: Tests for antibodies to both herpes simplex virus type 1 (typically oral) and type 2 (typically genital) to determine past or current infection.

name: Herpes Simplex I/II, IgM
description: Tests for IgM antibodies to herpes simplex virus types 1 and 2, which may indicate a recent or current active infection.

name: HIV-1 Rna, Qual. PCR
description: Uses PCR technology to directly detect HIV-1 virus genetic material in the blood. Particularly useful for early infection detection before antibodies develop.

name: HIV-1 /HIV -2 AG/AB Combo With Reflexes
description: Screening test that detects both HIV antigens and antibodies for both HIV-1 and HIV-2 types, with automatic follow-up testing if initial results are positive.

name: HIV1/ HIV2 Discrim Immuno
description: Confirmatory test that differentiates between HIV-1 and HIV-2 infections. Usually performed after a positive screening test.

name: Homocysteine, Total
description: Measures levels of homocysteine in the blood, which is associated with heart disease, stroke, and vitamin deficiencies when elevated.

name: HPV High Risk, Thinprep
description: Tests for high-risk strains of human papillomavirus (HPV) that are associated with cervical cancer using ThinPrep collection method.

name: HSV 1/2 PNL IGG/IGM
description: Herpes Simplex Virus panels for both types 1 and 2, testing for both IgG and IgM antibodies - Helps diagnose current or past HSV infections.

name: HSV I Glycoprotein G AB, IGG
description: Test for IgG antibodies against HSV-1 (oral herpes) - Determines if you've had a past infection with HSV-1.

name: HSV II Glycoprotein G AB, IGG
description: Test for IgG antibodies against HSV-2 (genital herpes) - Determines if you've had a past infection with HSV-2.

name: HSV - 2 IGG Inhib, Elisa
description: Specialized confirmatory ELISA test for HSV-2 IgG antibodies - Used when standard HSV-2 test results need verification or are unclear.

name: Immunog/ Streptoccus Typ A
description: Rapid test for detecting Group A Streptococcus bacteria - Used to diagnose strep throat infections.

name: Iron
description: Measures iron levels in blood - Used to evaluate iron deficiency or iron overload conditions.

name: Iron Profile
description: Comprehensive panel measuring iron, iron-binding capacity, and saturation - Provides complete picture of iron status for diagnosing iron deficiency or overload.

name: Iron Profile W/Ferritin
description: Extended iron panel including ferritin (iron storage protein) - Provides the most complete assessment of iron status and body iron stores.

name: Iron/ TIBC
description: Measures iron and total iron binding capacity - Helps diagnose iron deficiency anemia and other iron-related disorders.

name: LDL Cholesterol Direct
description: Direct measurement of LDL ("bad") cholesterol - More accurate than calculated LDL, especially when triglycerides are high.

name: Lead, Blood (Venous)
description: Measures lead concentration in blood - Used to screen for lead poisoning or exposure, especially important for children.

name: Lead/Fep
description: Measures lead and free erythrocyte protoporphyrin (FEP) - Comprehensive evaluation for lead exposure and its biological effects.

name: Lipase
description: Measures lipase enzyme levels - Used primarily to diagnose pancreatitis (inflammation of the pancreas).

name: Lipids Panel (AMA)
description: Comprehensive cholesterol panel including total cholesterol, HDL, LDL, triglycerides, and ratios - Standard screening for heart disease risk.

name: Lithium
description: Measures lithium concentration in blood - Monitors levels in patients taking lithium for bipolar disorder or depression.

name: Lupus Profile 1292
description: Comprehensive panel of antibody tests for lupus diagnosis - Includes ANA, dsDNA, SM, SM/RNP, SSA, and SSB antibodies.

name: Lutenizing Hormone(LH)
description: Measures luteinizing hormone levels - Important for evaluating fertility, menstrual problems, and pituitary function.

name: Lyme Comprehensive Prof
description: Comprehensive testing for Lyme disease - Multiple test methods to maximize detection of Borrelia burgdorferi infection.

name: Lyme Disease
description: Basic screening test for Lyme disease - Initial test to detect antibodies against the bacteria that causes Lyme disease.

name: Lyme IgG & IgM
description: Tests for both IgG and IgM antibodies against Lyme disease bacteria - Helps distinguish between recent and past infections.

name: Lyme IgG & IgM, IB
description: Western blot (immunoblot) confirmatory test for Lyme disease - Used to verify positive results from initial Lyme screening tests.

name: Lyme Modified Two-Tier
description: Newer, more sensitive two-step testing approach for Lyme disease - Improves detection of early Lyme infections.

name: Magnesium
description: Measures magnesium levels in blood - Important for heart rhythm, muscle function, bone health, and nervous system function.

name: Malarial Smear
description: Microscopic examination of blood for malaria parasites - Used to diagnose malaria in patients with fever who have traveled to endemic areas.

name: Measles IgG
description: Tests for immunity to measles (rubeola) - Determines if you have protection from previous vaccination or infection.

name: Measles/ Mumps/ Rubella Titres-MMR
description: Measures antibody levels for measles, mumps, and rubella - Determines immunity status for all three diseases, often used for healthcare workers or college entry.

name: Methadone, Quant, Ur
description: Quantitative measurement of methadone in urine - Monitors treatment compliance in methadone maintenance programs.

name: Methamphetamines Conf
description: Confirmation test for methamphetamines - Provides definitive results when screening tests are positive for methamphetamines.

name: Monkeypox Virus, PCR
description: PCR test that detects the genetic material of monkeypox virus - Used to diagnose active monkeypox infection.

name: Mumps Antibodies, IGG
description: Tests for immunity to mumps - Determines if you have protection from previous vaccination or infection.

name: Myco/Ureaplasma Culture
description: Culture test for Mycoplasma and Ureaplasma bacteria - Used to diagnose genital infections that may cause urinary symptoms or infertility.

name: Mycoplasma Genitalium
description: Tests specifically for Mycoplasma genitalium bacteria - Detects this sexually transmitted infection that can cause urethritis and cervicitis.

name: N. Gonorrhoeae Ampl, Urn
description: Urine test for gonorrhea using DNA amplification techniques - Non-invasive way to test for gonorrhea infection.

name: N.Gonorrheae,Amplified
description: Highly sensitive test for gonorrhea bacteria using DNA amplification - Used to diagnose gonorrhea infection from swab samples.

name: Neisseria Gonorrhoeae PCR
description: PCR test for detecting gonorrhea bacteria - Highly accurate DNA-based test for gonorrhea infection.

name: Nicotine, Serum
description: Measures nicotine and its metabolites in blood - Used to assess tobacco use or exposure to second-hand smoke.

name: Occult Blood-Feces 1 Smpl
description: Tests for hidden blood in stool - Screening test for colorectal cancer and other digestive tract conditions.

name: Oneswab BV Profile
description: Comprehensive test for bacterial vaginosis including Lactobacillus assessment - Single swab test providing detailed analysis of vaginal microbiome.

name: Opiates, Quant, Ur
description: Quantitative measurement of opiate drugs in urine - Precisely measures levels of opioid substances for medical or legal purposes.

name: Ova/ Parasite/ Giardia
description: Comprehensive stool test for parasites including Giardia - Detects parasitic infections that cause digestive symptoms.

name: Ova/ Parasites, Feces
description: Stool examination for parasitic eggs and organisms - Used to diagnose parasitic infections of the digestive tract.

name: Oxycodone Confirmation
description: Confirmation test for oxycodone - Verifies presence of oxycodone when screening tests are positive.

name: Partial Thromboplastin
description: Measures how long it takes blood to clot - Screens for bleeding disorders and monitors heparin therapy.

name: Parvovirus B19 IgG/IgM
description: Tests for both recent and past infections with parvovirus B19 - Helps diagnose Fifth disease or complications in pregnancy or anemia.

name: Parvovirus IgG
description: Tests for past infection with parvovirus B19 - Determines if you have immunity from previous exposure.

name: Parvovirus IgM
description: Tests for recent infection with parvovirus B19 - Helps diagnose active or recent Fifth disease.

name: Phencyclidine(PCP) Conf
description: Confirmation test for PCP (angel dust) - Verifies presence of PCP when screening tests are positive.

name: Phosphorus
description: Measures phosphorus levels in blood - Important for bone health, kidney function, and cellular energy processes.

name: Platelet Count
description: Counts platelets in blood - Important for assessing bleeding risk and clotting ability.

name: Potassium
description: Measures potassium levels in blood - Critical electrolyte for heart and muscle function.

name: Pregnancy Test, Serum
description: Blood test for pregnancy - Detects hCG hormone in blood to confirm pregnancy, more sensitive than urine tests.

name: Pregnancy Test, Urine
description: Urine test for pregnancy - Detects hCG hormone in urine to confirm pregnancy.

name: Prolactin
description: Measures prolactin hormone levels - Used to diagnose causes of abnormal milk production, menstrual problems, or infertility.

name: Protein/Creat Clear-24hr
description: Measures protein and creatinine clearance over 24 hours - Evaluates kidney function and protein leakage.

name: Prothrombin Time w/ INR
description: Measures blood clotting time with standardized ratio - Used to monitor warfarin therapy and assess liver function.

name: PSA Diagnostic
description: Prostate-specific antigen test - Used to help diagnose prostate cancer and monitor treatment effectiveness.

name: PSA Total
description: Measures total prostate-specific antigen in blood - Used to screen for prostate cancer and monitor prostate conditions.

name: PSA W/ Free PSA & Ratio
description: Measures total and free PSA with calculated ratio - Enhanced prostate cancer assessment, especially when total PSA is borderline.

name: PSA, Free & Total
description: Measures both free and total PSA levels - Helps differentiate between prostate cancer and benign prostate conditions.

name: Pseudocholinesterase
description: Measures pseudocholinesterase enzyme levels - Used before surgery to identify people at risk for prolonged paralysis from certain anesthetics.

name: PTT, Inhib Screen
description: Tests for inhibitors that interfere with blood clotting - Used to diagnose certain bleeding disorders including hemophilia.

name: Quantiferon-TB Goldplus, 4
description: Advanced blood test for tuberculosis infection - More specific than skin tests and unaffected by BCG vaccination.

name: Respiratory Panel PCR
description: Comprehensive test that detects multiple respiratory viruses including influenza A/B, RSV, and human metapneumovirus - Helps diagnose the cause of respiratory infections.

name: RH Factor
description: Determines if your blood has the Rh protein - Important during pregnancy to prevent complications if mother is Rh negative and baby is Rh positive.

name: Rheumatoid Factor
description: Detects antibodies associated with rheumatoid arthritis - Helps diagnose inflammatory autoimmune conditions affecting joints.

name: Rocky Mt. Spotted Fever
description: Tests for antibodies to the bacteria causing Rocky Mountain spotted fever - Important for diagnosing this tick-borne illness that causes fever and rash.

name: RPR
description: Rapid Plasma Reagin test for syphilis screening - Includes reflex testing if positive to confirm diagnosis of this sexually transmitted infection.

name: RSV - PCR
description: Detects genetic material of Respiratory Syncytial Virus - Accurate test for diagnosing RSV infections, which can be severe in infants and elderly.

name: PSV/ HMV
description: Tests for Respiratory Syncytial Virus and Human Metapneumovirus - Two common causes of respiratory infections, particularly in children.

name: Rubella IgG Antibody
description: Checks for immunity to rubella (German measles) - Important for women planning pregnancy to determine vaccination needs.

name: Sars-Cov-2 Antibodies
description: Detects antibodies to the virus that causes COVID-19 - Indicates past infection or immune response to vaccination.

name: Sars-Cov-2 Spike (S) AB
description: Specific test for antibodies against the spike protein of COVID-19 - Often used to check immune response after vaccination.

name: Scleroderma Antibody
description: Tests for Scl-70 antibodies associated with scleroderma - Helps diagnose this autoimmune disease causing skin and tissue hardening.

name: Sedimentation Rate
description: Measures how quickly red blood cells settle - A general indicator of inflammation in the body used to monitor inflammatory conditions.

name: Sero Type
description: Identifies specific strains or types of bacteria or viruses - Helps determine appropriate treatment for infections.

name: Sex Binding Globulin
description: Measures Sex Hormone Binding Globulin levels - Helps evaluate testosterone availability and diagnose hormonal imbalances.

name: Sickle Cell Screen
description: Screens for sickle cell trait or disease - Identifies if you carry or have this inherited red blood cell disorder.

name: Sjogren's Syndrome Panel
description: Tests for antibodies associated with Sjogren's syndrome - Helps diagnose this autoimmune condition causing dry eyes and mouth.

name: Sodium
description: Measures sodium levels in blood - Important for monitoring kidney function, dehydration, and electrolyte balance.

name: Spec Occupational Allergy
description: Comprehensive panel testing for allergies to workplace substances - Helps identify occupational allergies to chemicals, plants, and other materials.

name: Spec Std Package/Bundle
description: Comprehensive STD testing bundle including hepatitis B/C, syphilis, HIV, herpes, and common bacterial infections - Complete screening for sexual health.

name: Special Abnormal Thyroid
description: Advanced thyroid testing panel including antibodies and specialized markers - For complex thyroid disorders not diagnosed by basic testing.

name: Special Hyper Coagulabili
description: Tests for conditions that increase blood clotting risk - Evaluates multiple factors to identify causes of abnormal blood clotting or thrombosis.

name: Special Profile # 2770
description: Food allergy profile testing for common allergens - Screens for IgE antibodies to foods like shellfish, nuts, grains, and dairy products.

name: APTT
description: Activated Partial Thromboplastin Time with Prothrombin Time - Evaluates blood clotting abilities and monitors anticoagulant medications.

name: Special Profile 751
description: Anemia profile testing iron levels, B vitamins, and related factors - Comprehensive evaluation to determine causes of anemia or low red blood cell count.

name: Special STD Profile
description: Comprehensive sexually transmitted disease panel - Tests for herpes, chlamydia, gonorrhea, hepatitis C, syphilis, and HIV.

name: Sputum With Grm Stain
description: Analysis of coughed-up mucus with Gram stain - Identifies bacterial infections in lungs or airways based on microscopic examination.

name: SSA Antibody
description: Tests for Sjogren's syndrome A antibodies - Helps diagnose autoimmune disorders including Sjogren's syndrome and lupus.

name: SSB Antibody
description: Tests for Sjogren's syndrome B antibodies - Another marker for autoimmune conditions like Sjogren's syndrome and lupus.

name: Strep Screen Throat , Culture
description: Tests for strep throat infection with throat culture - More thorough than rapid strep tests for confirming streptococcal infection.

name: T-3 Uptake
description: Measures the binding capacity of thyroid hormone in blood - Helps evaluate thyroid function alongside other thyroid tests.

name: T-3, Free
description: Measures the unbound (active) form of the T3 thyroid hormone - More accurate indicator of thyroid function than total T3.

name: T-3,Total
description: Measures the total amount of triiodothyronine (T3) hormone - Helps diagnose hyperthyroidism and monitor thyroid treatment.

name: T-4
description: Measures total thyroxine (T4) hormone levels - Basic thyroid test to evaluate thyroid function and diagnose disorders.

name: T. Pallidium ABS, IgG/ IgM
description: Tests for antibodies to the bacterium causing syphilis - Specific test to confirm syphilis infection or past exposure.

name: T. Vaginalis Amplified
description: Tests for Trichomonas vaginalis, a common sexually transmitted parasite - Uses DNA amplification for accurate detection.

name: T4/ TSH
description: Measures both thyroid hormone T4 and Thyroid Stimulating Hormone - Basic thyroid function evaluation for diagnosing hypo/hyperthyroidism.

name: Testosterone
description: Measures total testosterone hormone levels - Important for evaluating male hormonal health, fertility issues, and certain conditions in women.

name: Testosterone Profile
description: Comprehensive testosterone evaluation including total, free, and bioavailable testosterone - Detailed assessment of testosterone status and binding proteins.

name: Tetanus Toxoid AB
description: Measures antibodies to tetanus toxoid - Determines if you have immunity to tetanus or need vaccination.

name: Thalassemia/ HBG Eval, S /WB
description: Evaluates for thalassemia and hemoglobin variants - Comprehensive testing for inherited blood disorders affecting hemoglobin production.

name: THC (Marijuana) Confirm
description: Confirmation test for marijuana (cannabis) use - Quantitative measurement of THC metabolites to verify positive screening results.

name: Thin Prep, HPV, GC Trich, CH
description: Comprehensive cervical screening including Pap test, HPV, gonorrhea, trichomoniasis, and chlamydia - Complete women's reproductive health screening.

name: Thin Prep/HPV
description: Pap smear with HPV testing - Screens for cervical cancer risk factors including precancerous cell changes and high-risk HPV strains.

name: Thinprep Pap
description: Modern liquid-based Pap smear - Screens for abnormal cervical cells that may indicate cancer or precancerous conditions.

name: Thinprep W/ HR-HPV/ GC, CT
description: Pap test with high-risk HPV, gonorrhea, and chlamydia testing - Comprehensive cervical and STI screening for women's health.

name: Throat Culture With Sens
description: Throat culture with antibiotic sensitivity testing - Identifies throat infections and determines which antibiotics will be effective.

name: Thyroglobulin, Serum, Qt.
description: Measures thyroglobulin protein levels - Used to monitor thyroid cancer after treatment or surgery.

name: Thyroid Antibody Panel
description: Tests for antibodies that attack the thyroid - Helps diagnose autoimmune thyroid disorders like Hashimoto's or Graves' disease.

name: Thyroid Function Test
description: Comprehensive evaluation of thyroid hormones and related measures - Complete assessment of thyroid function for diagnosing various disorders.

name: Thyroid Panel, Hypo
description: Focused panel to diagnose hypothyroidism - Measures TSH and Free T4 which are most important for detecting underactive thyroid.

name: Thyroid Profile
description: Basic thyroid function panel - Includes T4, T3 uptake, and TSH to evaluate overall thyroid function.

name: Thyroid Profile
description: Advanced thyroid evaluation with Free T4, TSH, and Free T3 - More complete assessment for complex thyroid disorders.

name: Thyroid Profile-Comp
description: Comprehensive thyroid panel including all major thyroid hormones - Complete evaluation for diagnosing various thyroid disorders.

name: Acute Tick - Borne Diseases (No Miyamotoi) PCR Panel
description: Tests for multiple tick-borne infections including Babesia, Anaplasma, Ehrlichia, and Borrelia species - Comprehensive panel for tick exposure.

name: Total Protein
description: Measures all proteins in blood plasma - General health indicator for nutrition, liver, and kidney function.

name: TP PAP GC Chlym Profile
description: ThinPrep Pap test with HPV and STI testing - Comprehensive women's health screening including cervical cancer and infection screening.

name: TP-PA Syphilis
description: Treponema pallidum particle agglutination test - Confirmation test for syphilis that remains positive for life after infection.

name: Trichomonas Vaginalis
description: Tests for Trichomonas vaginalis parasite - Common sexually transmitted infection causing vaginal or urethral inflammation.

name: TSH Receptor Antibody
description: Measures antibodies that target TSH receptors - Key test for diagnosing Graves' disease causing hyperthyroidism.

name: TSH W/Reflex Free T4
description: Initial TSH test that automatically adds Free T4 testing if results are abnormal - Efficient screening approach for thyroid disorders.

name: TSH, Ultrasensitive
description: Highly sensitive test measuring thyroid stimulating hormone - Primary screening test for thyroid disorders.

name: TSI Level
description: Thyroid Stimulating Immunoglobulin test - Helps diagnose Graves' disease, an autoimmune condition causing overactive thyroid.

name: UA, UA Culture, Ct, Sens
description: Urinalysis with culture and sensitivity testing - Checks for urinary tract infections and determines which antibiotics would be most effective.

name: Urea Nitrogen
description: Measures the amount of urea nitrogen in blood - Helps evaluate kidney function and assess hydration status.

name: Ureaplasma Urealyticum PC
description: Tests for the presence of Ureaplasma urealyticum bacteria - Often associated with urinary tract infections and reproductive system issues.

name: Uric Acid
description: Measures uric acid levels in blood - Helps diagnose gout, kidney stones, and certain metabolic disorders.

name: Urinalysis, Complete
description: Comprehensive testing of urine samples - Evaluates physical, chemical, and microscopic properties to detect various conditions including UTIs, kidney disease, and diabetes.

name: Urinalysis (No Micro), Chemistry Only
description: Basic chemical analysis of urine without microscopic examination - Tests for abnormalities like protein, glucose, and blood in urine.

name: Urine Culture
description: Tests urine for bacterial growth - Identifies specific bacteria causing urinary tract infections and determines effective treatments.

name: Urine Microalbumin, Random
description: Measures small amounts of protein (albumin) in urine - Early indicator of kidney damage, particularly in diabetic patients.

name: Urogen Urea/Mycoplasma
description: Tests for urogenital infection with Mycoplasma bacteria - Associated with urinary and reproductive tract infections.

name: Vaginitis Plus STI, TMA
description: Comprehensive test for vaginal infections and sexually transmitted infections - Detects bacterial vaginosis, candida, chlamydia, gonorrhea, and trichomoniasis using advanced molecular testing.

name: Varicella IgG
description: Tests for antibodies to varicella (chickenpox) virus - Determines immunity status from previous infection or vaccination.

name: Varicella IgM
description: Tests for recent infection with varicella (chickenpox) virus - IgM antibodies indicate current or very recent infection.

name: Varicella Zoster ABS(G/M)
description: Measures both IgG and IgM antibodies to varicella zoster virus - Evaluates both immunity status and possibility of recent infection for chickenpox or shingles.

name: Vitamin B-12
description: Measures vitamin B-12 levels in blood - Helps diagnose certain types of anemia, neurological disorders, and nutritional deficiencies.

name: Vitamin B-12 & Folate Serum
description: Measures both vitamin B-12 and folate levels - Important for evaluating causes of certain anemias and neurological conditions.

name: Vitamin B1, Plasma
description: Measures vitamin B1 (thiamine) levels in blood plasma - Helps diagnose thiamine deficiency which can cause neurological and cardiovascular problems.

name: Vitamin B6 Plasma Serum
description: Measures vitamin B6 (pyridoxine) levels in blood - Important for identifying B6 deficiency which can affect nervous system, metabolism, and immunity.

name: Vitamin D, 25-Hydroxy
description: Measures vitamin D levels in blood - The most accurate way to assess vitamin D status and detect deficiencies linked to bone health and other conditions.

name: Vitamin E, Serum/Plasma
description: Measures vitamin E levels in blood - Helps evaluate nutritional status and identify deficiencies that may affect nerve and muscle function.

name: Yeast Culture
description: Tests for the presence of yeast in a sample - Identifies yeast infections like candidiasis in various body sites.

name: Zika Virus, PCR (Serum)
description: Tests for Zika virus genetic material in blood - Used to confirm recent Zika virus infection, especially important for pregnant women.
